### CSS (styles.css)
css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

.container {
    width: 80%;
    margin: 0 auto;
}

header {
    background: #333;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 1rem 0;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
}

.nav-links {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
}

.nav-links a {
    color: #fff;
    text-decoration: none;
}

.about, .projects, .experience, .contact {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    text-align: center;
}

.project-grid {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.project {
    background: #f4f4f4;
    padding: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    border-radius: 5px;
    max-width: 30%;
}

.project img {
    max-width: 100%;
    border-radius: 5px;
}

.timeline {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: center;
}

.timeline-item {
    background: #f4f4f4;
    padding: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    border-radius: 5px;
    max-width: 600px;
    width: 100%;
}

.social-media {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
}

.social-media a img {
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
}

footer {
    background: #333;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 1rem 0;
    text-align: center;
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .project {
        max-width: 100%;
    }
}


### Explanation

1. *HTML Structure:*
   - The header contains navigation links.
   - Sections for About, Projects, Experience, and Contact.
   - Footer with copyright information.

2. *CSS Styling:*
   - Basic styling for body, container, header, and sections.
   - Flexbox for layout alignment in the header and project grid.
   - Responsive design using media queries for better display on smaller screens.

### Icons and Images:
- *Images:* Use placeholder images or your project images.
- *Icons:* Use free icon sets like FontAwesome or SVG icons for social media.

### Making it Responsive:
- The CSS includes media queries to adjust the layout for smaller screens.
- Flexbox is used to make layouts flexible and responsive.

By following this structure and style, youâ€™ll have a clean and responsive portfolio website that effectively showcases your work and experience.
